{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease a bundt tin or fluted ring cake tin (20 cm) and set aside.","Place almonds and fresh ginger into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>, or until finely chopped. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Without cleaning mixing bowl, place butter into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>2 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add all remaining ingredients, including reserved almond mixture, and mix <nobr>6 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <nobr>4 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, until combined.","Transfer mixture into prepared tin, smooth surface and bake for 30-35 minutes (160°C), or until a skewer inserted into the centre of the cake comes out clean. Allow cake to cool in tin for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g butter, cut into pieces (3-4 cm), plus extra for greasing","100 g raw almonds","2 - 3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","100 g brown sugar (see Tips)","190 g buttermilk","2 tsp natural vanilla extract","3 eggs","210 g spelt flour (see Tips)","1 tbsp ground ginger","2 tsp baking powder","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","2 tbsp lemon juice"]}],"id":"r123715","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-GiS8ms9zirU\/XZWrOwg6-hI\/AAAAAAAAfkU\/TjHA9cd5W7A66-oEolesI_DPYqORXQhiQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_gV9efFEfM5PtY77o.png","title":"Ginger bundt cake","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.8 g","fat":"14.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.8 g","calories":"1043 kJ \/ 248 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, bundt cake tin (20 cm), wooden or metal skewer, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can use your preferred brown sugar in this cake – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar.","The spelt flour can be substituted with regular plain flour if you prefer."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","1